# Launch Instance
# Create bucket in S3 for testing
# SSH to your Launched instance
:~$ sudo apt-get update -y
:~$ sudo apt-get install awscli
:~$ aws help (to check whether aws cli installed or not)
Click on your name tab and select My Security Credentials from the Aws Dashboard
Under Access keys (access key ID and secret access key) create New key and show access key
:~$ aws configure 
    1. AWS Access Key ID [None]: copy and paste Access key ID
    2. AWS Secret Access Key [None]: copy and paste secret access key
    3. Default region name [None]:
    4. Default region name [None]:
:~$ aws s3 ls (view s3 buckets in CLI)
:~$ aws s3 ls <bucket name> (view contain of bucket>
